      "post_content": "@ Donovan\\_Fabian No sir when a creature has wither counters, if it has -1/-1 counters equal to its toughness its sent to the graveyard as a state based action. Although it does remove damage, wither counters, and -1/-1 counters in general, are not considered damage. 704.5f If a creature has toughness 0 or less, it's put into its owner's graveyard. Regeneration can't replace this event.http://www.wizards.com/magic/comprules/MagicCompRules\\_20091005.txt However you're thinking very out of the box very commendable ^^.  \n  \n@ mn6334 It won't tap the creature unless it's destroyed, which is almost always better then having it tapped.  \n  \nAll this is a 6/6 for 7 multicolored creature I'd prefer a 5/5 or 5/4 for 6 instead so it couldn't be compared to [Spearbreaker Behemoth](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spearbreaker Behemoth) which is just different, that being said I would never take Mr Plowbeasts over Spearbreaker in my white green deck.",
